org.neo4j.function

Interface UnaryOperator<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the operand and result of the operator
    All Superinterfaces:
    Function<T,T>, RawFunction<T,T,RuntimeException>, ThrowingFunction<T,T,RuntimeException>, ThrowingUnaryOperator<T,RuntimeException>

    public interface UnaryOperator<T>
extends Function<T,T>, ThrowingUnaryOperator<T,RuntimeException>
    Represents an operation on a single operand that produces a result of the same type as its operand. This is a specialization of @{link Function} for the case where the operand and result are of the same type.
